content_html:
Sprint 2

Planning

Sprint Duration: 2 week (4/4/2022 - 4/16/2022)

Scrum Masters: Aditya Desai, Srikar Vodeti, Achuth Reddy Rajula, Mohammed Sarfraz Pattan, Gautham Krishna

Goal

The goal for sprint 2 is to add Cycle-time, Active Tasks microservices into the app both on frontend and on backend. Also, revise Niko-Niko and Lead Time from GET to POST request. Also enable CI/CD for first microservices.

Review

Demo Video Link: https://asu.zoom.us/rec/share/Qir0Sp4olMuGuJwxK99Fmmx8sv_oi9btSAhdtcDOx0U40ggfH6RVjvbpMRdMAPOl.Z9OzIvY85t-gGFOy?startTime=1650335466000      
Passcode: GPej&87i

Is The Sprint Goal Achieved: Yes

Screenshot of Final Sprint Board: 

Screenshot of Final Burndown Chart:

A List of User Stores Not Completed: US#8, US#40

Retrospective

What got accomplished: 

  1. Disintegrated Taiga integration team.
  2. Communication within the team as well as on the top level has been improved.

What didn’t get accomplished: 

  1. Burndown chart was not consistent as top-level scrum board is not being updated frequently.
  2. More documentation on team level and top-level.

What could be improved / insights learned: 

  1. Communication at the top-level is to be improved more.
  2. Update tasks frequently, such that burndown chart looks better.
  3. Final integration could go a little bit smooth.

Scrum Masters Meeting Minutes

Date&Time Attendees Topics
8/4/2022, 6:30-7:30PM Aditya Desai, Gautham Krishna, Achuth Reddy Rajula, Mohammed Pattan Team 1: CI/CD prototype working, Codiga done, update COR policy on api. Team 2: Niko Niko is done but API server is not up will done with that today. Active task metric is being done will be completed by Monday. Team 4: Lead time delivered. Cycle time in progress, ETD 12th April EOD. Team 5: Integrated ‘leadTime’ micro service into the web app. CORS configuration request to API Gateway. Had a discussion with micro service teams about how we can build more efficient flow by next version. Working to integrate 3 more micro services.
17/4/2022, 6:30-7:30PM Lor Worwag, Gautham Krishna, Achuth Reddy Rajula, Mohammed Pattan, Srikar Vodeti Team 1, developing a pipeline for continuous integration and deployment, add all endpoints of microservices to API Gateway. Team 2, develop Scope change metric, develop Accepted work spread, deliver Active tasks. Team 3, develop impediment tracker. Team 4, develop throughput metric. Team 5, integrate and visualize all the above metrics.

Code Quality

The average quality score of all is about 91% which is less than the required threshold, the average code distribution of all is about 5932 lines of code which is less than the required threshold, the average technical debt of all is about $1271 which is less than the required threshold. Also to mention, test cases only for microservices. To see more about the code quality on each team, please to go each teams wiki page.
